### 4.2 Mermaid Diagram — Object Lifecycle State Machine

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> ClassLoading : ClassLoader triggered
    ClassLoading --> ClassLinked : Verification, Preparation, Resolution
    ClassLinked --> ClassInitialised : Static fields assigned, <clinit> executed
    ClassInitialised --> ReadyForUse : Class available in Method Area

    ReadyForUse --> ObjectInstantiation : new keyword invoked
    ObjectInstantiation --> MemoryAllocated : Heap space reserved
    MemoryAllocated --> DefaultInit : Fields set to defaults (0, null, false)
    DefaultInit --> ExplicitInit : Instance initializer blocks run
    ExplicitInit --> ConstructorExecuted : Constructor body executes
    ConstructorExecuted --> InUse : Object reference returned to caller

    InUse --> InUse : Methods invoked, fields modified
    InUse --> Unreachable : All references set to null / out of scope
    Unreachable --> GarbageCollected : GC discovers object (Mark phase)
    GarbageCollected --> Finalized : finalize() called (deprecated)
    Finalized --> MemoryReclaimed : Sweep phase, memory returned to heap
    MemoryReclaimed --> [*]

    note right of ClassInitialised
        Static fields get default values
        during Preparation phase
    end note

    note right of ExplicitInit
        Field initializers execute
        in order of declaration
    end note

    note right of ConstructorExecuted
        First statement must be
        this(...) or super(...)
    end note

    note right of Unreachable
        Only eligible, not yet
        collected by GC
    end note
```

