**Q1. [KTU University Exam - Dec 2023]**

**Differentiate between a class and an object in Java. Illustrate with a suitable example.**

**Model Answer (3 marks):**

| Aspect | Class | Object |
|---|---|---|
| **Definition** | A blueprint or template that defines the structure (fields) and behaviour (methods) of entities. | A runtime instance of a class occupying actual memory. |
| **Memory** | No memory is allocated when a class is defined. Logical entity only. | Memory is allocated in the heap when `new` is invoked. Physical entity. |
| **Declaration** | Declared once using the `class` keyword. | Created as many times as needed using `new ClassName()`. |
| **Keyword** | Defined by `class` keyword. | Created using `new` keyword. |
| **Example** | `class Car { ... }` | `Car myCar = new Car();` |

**Example Illustration:**
```java
class Car {                  // CLASS — blueprint
    String color;
    void drive() { System.out.println("Driving"); }
}

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Car c1 = new Car();   // OBJECT 1 — instance
        Car c2 = new Car();   // OBJECT 2 — another instance
        c1.color = "Red";
        c2.color = "Blue";
    }
}
```
Here, `Car` is the class. `c1` and `c2` are two distinct objects (instances) of `Car`, each with its own `color` value.

