**Q2. [KTU University Exam - June 2023]**

**Explain the significance of the `this` keyword in Java. List any four uses.**

**Model Answer (3 marks):**

The `this` keyword in Java is a **reference variable** that refers to the **current object** — the one on which a method or constructor is being invoked. It is an implicit final reference automatically passed to every instance method and constructor.

**Four Uses of `this`:**

1. **Differentiating instance variables from local variables/parameters:**
   ```java
   void setName(String name) { this.name = name; }
   ```

2. **Invoking a constructor of the current class (constructor chaining):**
   ```java
   Student() { this("Default", 0); }  // calls parameterized constructor
   ```

3. **Returning the current object from a method (used in fluent API design):**
   ```java
   public Student setName(String n) { this.name = n; return this; }
   ```

4. **Passing the current object as a parameter to another method:**
   ```java
   register(this);  // passes current object
   ```

