### Model Solution for Question B:

#### Part (a) — Checked vs Unchecked Exceptions

| Parameter | Checked Exceptions | Unchecked Exceptions |
|---|---|---|
| **Detection** | Compile-time | Runtime |
| **Handling** | Mandatory (try-catch or throws) | Optional |
| **Parent Class** | Direct subclass of `Exception` | Subclass of `RuntimeException` |
| **Examples** | `IOException`, `SQLException`, `ClassNotFoundException` | `ArithmeticException`, `NullPointerException`, `ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException` |
| **Compiler enforcement** | Yes | No |

**Example of Checked:**
```java
import java.io.*;
class CheckedDemo {
    public static void main(String[] args) throws IOException {  // Must declare
        FileReader fr = new FileReader("test.txt");
    }
}
```

**Example of Unchecked:**
```java
class UncheckedDemo {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int result = 10 / 0;  // ArithmeticException at runtime
        System.out.println(result);
    }
}
```

