## 5.3 ⚠️ KTU Examiner's Valuation Warning / Pitfall Callout

> [!WARNING]
> **Common Mistakes That Cost Marks:**
> 
> 1. **Forgetting `setVisible(true)`** — The most common error. Without this call, the JFrame exists in memory but is never displayed. (Lose 1-2 marks)
> 
> 2. **Forgetting `setDefaultCloseOperation(EXIT_ON_CLOSE)`** — The window will not terminate the JVM when closed; the program continues running invisibly. Use `EXIT_ON_CLOSE` for full application exit or `DISPOSE_ON_CLOSE` for window-only closure.
> 
> 3. **Confusing `getText()` with `getLabel()`** — `JTextField` uses `getText()`/`setText()`; `JLabel` uses `getText()`/`setText()` too, but you cannot edit a JLabel's text at runtime in the GUI (it's not editable by user). Don't confuse with `JTextArea` either.
> 
> 4. **Not implementing `actionPerformed` when the class declares `implements ActionListener`** — Compile-time error. The class must provide this method.
> 
> 5. **Writing `addActionListener(new ActionListener())` incorrectly** — Forgetting the `new` keyword or missing the semicolon after the closing brace `};`.
> 
> 6. **Using AWT components (`Button`, `TextField`) instead of Swing (`JButton`, `JTextField`)** — KTU syllabus specifies Swing. AWT components are heavyweight and platform-dependent. Always use `javax.swing.*` components.
> 
> 7. **Forgetting exception handling for `Integer.parseInt()`** — If the user enters non-numeric text, a `NumberFormatException` is thrown. Always wrap in `try-catch`.
> 
> 8. **Confusing Adapter with Listener** — `MouseAdapter` is a **class** (extend it), `MouseListener` is an **interface** (implement it). Common confusion in theory questions.

