## 2.3 The "Why" Behind JLabel Design

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **🎯 Why is JLabel Passive (Non-Interactive)?**
> In MVC architecture, `JLabel` serves as the **View** layer for **static descriptive data**. A label cannot generate `ActionEvent` because:
> 1. It has no **semantic action** — it merely describes or annotates.
> 2. It is often bound to a focused component via `setLabelFor()` — when the label's mnemonic is pressed, focus transfers to the bound component, but the label itself emits no event.
> 3. Performance: avoiding listener registration keeps lightweight components efficient.

**Real-world engineering utility:**
- **Form-based systems** (registration, login, admin panels): label each input field.
- **Dashboard GUIs**: show static data like version, status, user name.
- **Image display**: render logos, photos, status indicators.

