## 2.5 Mnemonic Concept — Critical for KTU

> [!NOTE]
> A **mnemonic** allows the user to interact with a component via the keyboard. For example, if a label has mnemonic `'N'`, pressing **Alt + N** will shift focus to the component associated via `setLabelFor()`.
>
> **Example:** A label "**N**ame:" with mnemonic `'N'` paired with a `JTextField` — pressing Alt+N places the cursor in the text field.

```java
JLabel nameLbl = new JLabel("Name:");
nameLbl.setDisplayedMnemonic('N');   // 'N' will be underlined (look-and-feel dependent)
nameLbl.setLabelFor(nameField);       // Pressing Alt+N focuses nameField
```
