## 3.2 Walkthrough 2: JLabel with Text + Icon + Mnemonic

### Problem Statement
Create a login form prototype with a `JLabel` "**U**sername:" that uses 'U' as a mnemonic, displays a user icon to its left, and on Alt+U activation transfers focus to an adjacent `JTextField`.

### Solution Code

```java
import javax.swing.*;
import java.awt.*;

public class LabelIconMnemonicDemo extends JFrame {
    public LabelIconMnemonicDemo() {
        // Step 1: Create a JTextField
        JTextField userField = new JTextField(15);

        // Step 2: Create a JLabel with text, icon, and horizontal alignment
        ImageIcon userIcon = new ImageIcon("user.png");   // Replace with a valid image path
        JLabel userLabel = new JLabel("Username:", userIcon, SwingConstants.LEFT);

        // Step 3: Set the mnemonic key to 'U' (note: use KeyEvent.VK_U for portability)
        userLabel.setDisplayedMnemonic('U');

        // Step 4: Set icon-text gap to 8 pixels
        userLabel.setIconTextGap(8);

        // Step 5: Bind the label to the text field
        userLabel.setLabelFor(userField);

        // Step 6: Place components in a panel with FlowLayout
        JPanel panel = new JPanel(new FlowLayout(FlowLayout.LEFT));
        panel.add(userLabel);
        panel.add(userField);

        // Step 7: Configure frame
        add(panel);
        setTitle("Label with Icon & Mnemonic");
        setSize(400, 100);
        setDefaultCloseOperation(JFrame.EXIT_ON_CLOSE);
        setVisible(true);
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        new LabelIconMnemonicDemo();
    }
}
```

### Analytical Matrix — Line-by-Line Reasoning

| Line | Code | Reasoning |
|---|---|---|
| `new ImageIcon("user.png")` | Loads an image from the working directory; alternative: pass `URL` or `Image` |
| `new JLabel("Username:", userIcon, SwingConstants.LEFT)` | Uses the **3-arg constructor** combining text + icon + alignment — most commonly asked in KTU |
| `setDisplayedMnemonic('U')` | Defines 'U' as the Alt-keyboard shortcut; the letter U in the label is automatically **underlined** (look-and-feel dependent) |
| `setIconTextGap(8)` | Adds 8 px of breathing space between icon and text |
| `setLabelFor(userField)` | **Critical accessibility binding** — pressing Alt+U now transfers keyboard focus to `userField` |
| `new JPanel(new FlowLayout(FlowLayout.LEFT))` | FlowLayout with LEFT alignment ensures label and field appear side-by-side |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **KTU Examiner Insight:** `setDisplayedMnemonic(char)` and `setLabelFor(Component)` together form an **accessibility feature** (a11y). Examiners may ask: *"Which method is used to associate a label with a component so that pressing the mnemonic key transfers focus?"* → Answer: **`setLabelFor()`**.

