## 3.3 Walkthrough 3: JLabel Position Relative to Icon (Text-Icon Layout)

### Problem Statement
Demonstrate all four combinations of `setHorizontalTextPosition` and `setVerticalTextPosition` to position text **relative to the icon**.

### Solution Code

```java
import javax.swing.*;
import java.awt.*;

public class TextPositionDemo extends JFrame {
    public TextPositionDemo() {
        setLayout(new GridLayout(2, 2, 10, 10));   // 2×2 grid with 10px gaps

        ImageIcon icon = new ImageIcon("java.png");

        // (a) Text to the RIGHT of icon
        JLabel l1 = new JLabel("Right", icon, SwingConstants.CENTER);
        l1.setHorizontalTextPosition(SwingConstants.RIGHT);
        l1.setVerticalTextPosition(SwingConstants.CENTER);

        // (b) Text to the LEFT of icon
        JLabel l2 = new JLabel("Left", icon, SwingConstants.CENTER);
        l2.setHorizontalTextPosition(SwingConstants.LEFT);
        l2.setVerticalTextPosition(SwingConstants.CENTER);

        // (c) Text ABOVE icon
        JLabel l3 = new JLabel("Top", icon, SwingConstants.CENTER);
        l3.setHorizontalTextPosition(SwingConstants.CENTER);
        l3.setVerticalTextPosition(SwingConstants.TOP);

        // (d) Text BELOW icon
        JLabel l4 = new JLabel("Bottom", icon, SwingConstants.CENTER);
        l4.setHorizontalTextPosition(SwingConstants.CENTER);
        l4.setVerticalTextPosition(SwingConstants.BOTTOM);

        add(l1); add(l2); add(l3); add(l4);

        setTitle("JLabel — Text Position Relative to Icon");
        setSize(600, 400);
        setDefaultCloseOperation(JFrame.EXIT_ON_CLOSE);
        setVisible(true);
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        new TextPositionDemo();
    }
}
```

### Analytical Matrix

| Sub-label | Method Calls | Visual Layout |
|---|---|---|
| **(a)** `Right` | `hTextPos = RIGHT`, `vTextPos = CENTER` | `[icon]  Right` |
| **(b)** `Left` | `hTextPos = LEFT`, `vTextPos = CENTER` | `Left  [icon]` |
| **(c)** `Top` | `hTextPos = CENTER`, `vTextPos = TOP` | `Top` over `[icon]` |
| **(d)** `Bottom` | `hTextPos = CENTER`, `vTextPos = BOTTOM` | `Bottom` under `[icon]` |

> [!NOTE]
> **Distinction (Frequently Confused):**
> - `setHorizontalAlignment` → Positions **text+icon together** within the label's display area.
> - `setHorizontalTextPosition` → Positions the **text relative to the icon** only.
> These are **two different** concepts. KTU questions often test this distinction.

