## 3.6 Event Handling — A Common KTU Pitfall

> [!WARNING]
> **❌ JLabel does NOT generate ActionEvents.**
> ```java
> // WRONG — This will NOT compile meaningfully
> userLabel.addActionListener(...);  // ❌ No such method on JLabel
> ```
>
> **✅ Workaround:** Bind a `JLabel`'s mnemonic to a `JButton` (or any focusable component). When the mnemonic is pressed, focus moves to the bound component. If that component is a `JButton`, it does **not** automatically click — you would need to invoke `doClick()` programmatically via a `KeyEvent` dispatcher, **or** simply use a `JButton` with `setMnemonic()` directly.

```java
// Mnemonic-only transfer (no automatic click)
nameLabel.setDisplayedMnemonic(KeyEvent.VK_N);
nameLabel.setLabelFor(submitButton);   // Alt+N moves focus to submitButton
```
