## 5.1 🅰️ Part A Questions (3 Marks Each)

### Question A1 `[KTU University Exam — June 2024]`
**Q: What is `JLabel` in Java Swing? List any two constructors of `JLabel` with their signatures.**

**Model Answer:**

`JLabel` is a passive component of `javax.swing` package, used to display a short text string, an image, or both on a GUI. It is a subclass of `JComponent` and does not generate events.

**Two constructors:**
1. `JLabel()` — Creates a label with no text and no icon.
2. `JLabel(String text)` — Creates a label initialized with the given text string.
3. *(Bonus third)* `JLabel(Icon image)` — Creates a label with the specified icon.

---

### Question A2 `[KTU University Exam — Dec 2023]`
**Q: Differentiate between `setHorizontalAlignment()` and `setHorizontalTextPosition()` of `JLabel`.**

**Model Answer:**

| Feature | `setHorizontalAlignment(int)` | `setHorizontalTextPosition(int)` |
|---|---|---|
| **Purpose** | Positions the **text+icon together** within the label's display area | Positions the **text relative to the icon** |
| **Default Value** | `LEADING` | `TRAILING` |
| **Used When** | Always applicable | Only meaningful when both text and icon are present |

**Example:**
```java
label.setHorizontalAlignment(SwingConstants.CENTER);        // icon+text both centered
label.setHorizontalTextPosition(SwingConstants.RIGHT);     // text shown to right of icon
```

