## 5.2 🅱️ Part B Questions (14 Marks Each — Internal Choice Pattern)

### Question A (14 Marks) `[KTU University Exam — Model Paper 2024]`

**(a)** Explain the class hierarchy of `JLabel` in Java Swing. Mention the package and the interfaces it implements. **(7 marks)**

**(b)** Write a Java Swing program to create a `JFrame` with a `JLabel` displaying the text *"Kerala Technological University"*, font Arial Bold 22, RED color, and CENTER-aligned. Also add a `JTextField` and bind the label to it using a mnemonic so that pressing **Alt+K** transfers focus to the text field. **(7 marks)**

---

#### Model Solution for (a) — Hierarchy

The class hierarchy of `JLabel` is:

```
java.lang.Object
   ↑ (extends)
java.awt.Component
   ↑ (extends)
java.awt.Container
   ↑ (extends)
javax.swing.JComponent
   ↑ (extends)
javax.swing.JLabel
```

- **Package:** `javax.swing`
- **Class signature:** `public class JLabel extends JComponent implements SwingConstants, Accessible`
- **`SwingConstants`** interface provides alignment constants: `LEFT`, `CENTER`, `RIGHT`, `TOP`, `BOTTOM`, `LEADING`, `TRAILING`.
- **`Accessible`** interface provides support for assistive technologies (screen readers), making `JLabel` accessibility-friendly.
- `JLabel` is a **lightweight component** (since `JComponent` does not peer with the underlying OS).

---

#### Model Solution for (b) — Code

```java
import javax.swing.*;
import java.awt.*;
import java.awt.event.KeyEvent;

public class KtuLabelDemo extends JFrame {
    public KtuLabelDemo() {
        // Text field
        JTextField textField = new JTextField(20);

        // Label
        JLabel label = new JLabel("Kerala Technological University");
        label.setFont(new Font("Arial", Font.BOLD, 22));
        label.setForeground(Color.RED);
        label.setHorizontalAlignment(SwingConstants.CENTER);

        // Mnemonic binding
        label.setDisplayedMnemonic(KeyEvent.VK_K);
        label.setLabelFor(textField);

        // Layout
        JPanel panel = new JPanel(new FlowLayout());
        panel.add(label);
        panel.add(textField);
        add(panel);

        setTitle("JLabel with Mnemonic Demo");
        setSize(500, 150);
        setDefaultCloseOperation(JFrame.EXIT_ON_CLOSE);
        setVisible(true);
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        new KtuLabelDemo();
    }
}
```

**Explanation of Key Steps:**
1. `JLabel` text is set in the constructor.
2. `setFont()` uses `Font.BOLD` (1) for bold style.
3. `setHorizontalAlignment(CENTER)` centers the text inside the label.
4. `setDisplayedMnemonic(KeyEvent.VK_K)` sets **Alt+K** as the keyboard shortcut.
5. `setLabelFor(textField)` binds the label to the text field — focus transfers on Alt+K.

