## 5.3 ⚠️ KTU Examiner's Valuation Warning / Pitfall Callout

> [!WARNING]
> **Common Mistakes That Cost Marks:**
>
> 1. **Confusing `setHorizontalAlignment` with `setHorizontalTextPosition`.** The former places the entire content; the latter places text *relative to icon*. Marks deducted for misuse.
>
> 2. **Forgetting `setOpaque(true)` before `setBackground()`.** JLabels are transparent by default; setting a background color without enabling opacity produces a no-op, and the examiner will mark it as incomplete.
>
> 3. **Writing `addActionListener` on a JLabel.** There is no such method. JLabels do not fire action events. Use `setLabelFor` + `setDisplayedMnemonic` for keyboard interaction.
>
> 4. **Forgetting to call `setVisible(true)`** on the JFrame at the end — the program compiles but never displays anything.
>
> 5. **Not closing the JFrame properly** — omitting `setDefaultCloseOperation(JFrame.EXIT_ON_CLOSE)` causes the window to close but the JVM keeps running, which is a frequent KTU practical exam mistake.
>
> 6. **Using `null` layout without bounds** — JLabel has no preferred size in many cases; if you set layout to `null`, you **must** also call `setSize()` / `setBounds()` on the label.
>
> 7. **Importing wrong classes** — `JLabel` is in `javax.swing`, not `java.awt`. Using `java.awt.Label` (the AWT version) is a frequently tested trap in KTU!

